CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 9, 1960, pg. 11, reads: "Explorer Scouts Ball - Explorer Scouts of Hill City held their annual ball recently at the Hotel Roosevelt. A few of the Scouts and their dated took time out from dancing to pose for The Courier photographer. Left to right, first row: Toni Bray, Elizabeth Pearson, Jacqueline Turk. Second row: Charles Morris, Paul Morris, Tony Gillcrese, Melvin Harvey, Richard Gillcrese, John Nelson and Edward Gray. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Explorer Scouts of Hill City including Toni Bray, Elizabeth Pearson, Jacqueline Turk in first row, and Charles Morris, Paul Morris, Tony Gillcrese, Melvin Harvey, Richard Gillcrese, John Nelson and Edward Gray in second row, posed in Hotel Roosevelt for ball
